  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "I want to be direct with you. While I can discuss regulatory compliance generally, providing specific legal advice would require consulting a qualified legal professional who understands the specific details of your situation.\n\nGenerally speaking, many jurisdictions have legal requirements for financial institutions and certain professions to report suspicious transactions that might indicate money laundering. These typically include:\n\n1. Filing Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n2. Identifying and verifying customer identities\n3. Maintaining transaction records\n4. Having internal anti-money laundering (AML) procedures\n\nThe specifics vary by country and sector. Financial professionals, banks, casinos, and other businesses often have mandatory reporting obligations.\n\nWould you like me to provide some general, publicly available information about money laundering reporting requirements?",
